```json
{
  "step1": "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan and line with parchment. In a large bowl, whisk together 1½ cups flour, ¾ cup cocoa powder, 1½ teaspoons baking soda, ½ teaspoon baking powder, and ½ teaspoon salt. Set aside.",
  "step2": "In a separate bowl, beat 3 large eggs, ¾ cup yellow sugar, ¼ cup white sugar, and 2 teaspoons vanilla extract until light and fluffy. Gradually add 1½ cups milk, ½ cup melted butter, and 1 cup plain yogurt. Mix until smooth.",
  "step3": "Combine the wet and dry mixtures, stirring until no lumps remain. Fold in 1 cup cold chocolate chips for added texture. Pour batter into prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula.",
  "step4": "Bake for 35‑40 minutes, checking doneness with a toothpick—it should come out clean or with a few crumbs. Remove from oven, let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.",
  "step5": "While still warm, spread a rich ganache made from ½ cup heavy cream and ½ cup chopped semi‑sweet chocolate over the top. Let the ganache set for 5 minutes before adding a light dusting of powdered sugar.",
  "step6": "Slice and serve. Store leftover pieces in an airtight container at room temperature for up to two days, or refrigerate for longer freshness."
}
```
